      <intermediateExchange id="08ed24e9-2d3a-5c3d-b5f7-56292da527ec" unitId="487df68b-4994-4027-8fdc-a4dc298257b7" amount="0.00041536" intermediateExchangeId="9cbe46b4-9041-4727-9f73-61138c1c7a0d" activityLinkId="73df7bc5-a0ad-5b2c-b761-60afd408b6af">
        <name xml:lang="en">packaging, for fertilisers or pesticides</name>
        <unitName xml:lang="en">kg</unitName>
        <comment xml:lang="en">25 kg woven PP bags are most used for fertiliser packaging. It is assumed conservatively 100 g/m2, add 10% extra for the edges overlap and cutting losses. It results in 0.50*0.80*2*1.1 = 0.88 m2/bag = 88 g/bag per 25 kg fertiliser. The sum of the solid fertiliser including lime and also the linseeds input is maximum of 762 kg/ha and harvest --&gt; 30.5 (31) bags would be required. In sum per ha and harvest hence 31 pieces * 88g/piece = 2.73 kg bags (conservatively). per kg flax plant harvested hence 0.00041536 kg PP bag,</comment>
